  "prefill_text": "The transformer architecture relies on scaled dot-product attention to model relationships between tokens. Each attention layer maintains key and value projections that are stored in a KV cache during autoregressive decoding. Quantizing this cache reduces memory bandwidth and enables longer context windows on fixed hardware. The TurboQuant approach applies Lloyd-Max scalar quantization after rotating activations with a learned orthogonal matrix, achieving compression ratios above 3x while preserving cosine similarity above 0.99 on validated model families including Llama, Mistral, Qwen, Phi, Gemma, and Molmo.",
